WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:20.540
Did you know there's an awesome treasure at the end of this sea?!

3
00:00:20.540 --> 00:00:23.340
And whoever gets it becomes King of the Pirates!

4
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:24.960
Isn't that exciting?!

5
00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.010
Cool new adventures are waiting out there!

6
00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:38.060
BON VOYAGE! Light the ember of courage and let the fire grow

7
00:00:38.060 --> 00:00:45.660
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

8
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:48.210
Back when we first started

9
00:00:48.210 --> 00:00:53.430
we had separate ideas about where we would soon go

10
00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:55.380
Things have changed now,

11
00:00:55.380 --> 00:01:00.440
when we look towards our dreams we all share one telescope

12
00:01:00.730 --> 00:01:05.680
When you find that your heart's been led astray

13
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:09.980
time to calibrate your compasses

14
00:01:09.980 --> 00:01:13.010
Set a new course, turn the tables now

15
00:01:13.010 --> 00:01:20.300
BON VOYAGE! Shed your previous baggage, forget the past

16
00:01:20.300 --> 00:01:27.140
Smiles can weather a storm, we know that better than anyone

17
00:01:27.140 --> 00:01:29.080
Don't you fret,

18
00:01:29.080 --> 00:01:34.900
tears shed along the way to your dreams are not in vain

19
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:41.100
You know that you're all PRECIOUS IN MY LIFE

20
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:49.210
I caught a glimpse at what's beyond the horizon

21
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:55.510
<b>I Made It Here</b>

22
00:01:58.930 --> 00:02:02.730
Four hundred years of fighting
had come to an end at last,

23
00:02:02.730 --> 00:02:07.270
and the Skypieans continued
their celebration for days on end.

24
00:02:08.780 --> 00:02:12.110
I... I... I can't drink any more...

25
00:02:17.030 --> 00:02:18.700
There they are!

26
00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:24.670
Hey!

27
00:02:27.250 --> 00:02:28.540
What is it?

28
00:02:28.540 --> 00:02:30.210
Nami, wake everyone up!

29
00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:32.970
Why?

30
00:02:34.930 --> 00:02:36.640
We're gonna steal the gold and run!

31
00:02:39.140 --> 00:02:40.470
There's gold?!

32
00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:42.060
Dummy! Keep it down!

33
00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:45.730
What do you mean "dummy"?!
You're louder than I am!

34
00:02:45.730 --> 00:02:48.980
Louder than you?!
You're the loud one!

35
00:02:48.980 --> 00:02:54.030
What?! You're calling me loud
when you're being super-duper loud?!

36
00:02:54.590 --> 00:02:58.070
It's your voice that's
super-mega-ultra loud!

37
00:02:58.070 --> 00:03:02.290
No way! The only reason I'm talking
so loud is because you're yelling!

38
00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:05.920
You were yelling first!
Shut up! I can't sleep!

39
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:07.580
So what?! You're still the loud one!

40
00:03:07.580 --> 00:03:09.170
Not me! It's you!

41
00:03:08.080 --> 00:03:10.460
Usopp hit me!

42
00:03:09.170 --> 00:03:13.590
I'm a delicate lady! I wouldn't yell
with my mouth wide open, would I?!

43
00:03:10.460 --> 00:03:11.380
What?!

44
00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:13.590
I'd never do that!

45
00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:16.800
See? See?! Your mouth is wide open!

46
00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:15.680
Don't accuse me of that!

47
00:03:14.670 --> 00:03:16.800
Geez, wake up, sleepyhead!

48
00:03:15.680 --> 00:03:17.510
But you did hit me!

49
00:03:16.800 --> 00:03:19.350
That's because you ticked me off!

50
00:03:17.510 --> 00:03:19.100
Right here, I felt it!

51
00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:19.800
Nami! Good morning!

52
00:03:19.100 --> 00:03:21.470
Yeah, yeah... Keep telling
yourself that, dummy.

53
00:03:19.350 --> 00:03:22.220
I just said you don't have to yell!

54
00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.220
Oh? It's not morning yet!

55
00:03:21.470 --> 00:03:23.220
What do you mean, "dummy"?!

56
00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:25.980
Blue Sea people sure like
to party, don't they?

57
00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:28.100
This is the fourth day in a row.

58
00:03:28.100 --> 00:03:30.440
Their stamina is incredible.

59
00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:38.990
So, that's the plan.

60
00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:42.450
Okay, guys! It's not often that
we get to visit a sky island!

61
00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:44.910
Make sure you don't
leave with any regrets!

62
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:51.590
Chief! We found the golden bell!

63
00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:53.000
What?!

64
00:03:53.880 --> 00:03:55.380
Hey, are you serious?!

65
00:03:55.380 --> 00:03:59.340
Yeah. It's stuck on
the fallen Giant Jack.

66
00:03:59.340 --> 00:04:01.800
We're pulling it out right now.

67
00:04:02.640 --> 00:04:04.930
If you can help,
come to the western shore!

68
00:04:04.930 --> 00:04:07.480
Hurry! Get a move on!

69
00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:10.150
Alright! Gather everyone!

70
00:04:10.860 --> 00:04:12.270
They found the bell!

71
00:04:12.270 --> 00:04:13.320
Where?!

72
00:04:13.320 --> 00:04:14.530
At the western shore.

73
00:04:14.530 --> 00:04:15.570
– Okay!
– Okay!

74
00:04:15.570 --> 00:04:16.280
Are you sure?!

75
00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:18.070
Yeah! Hurry up already!

76
00:04:18.530 --> 00:04:20.530
Apparently it fell into the sea!

77
00:04:20.530 --> 00:04:24.040
Yeah. Those who can move,
gather at the western shore!

78
00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:28.960
They found the bell!

79
00:04:28.960 --> 00:04:30.880
It's at the western shore!

80
00:04:31.630 --> 00:04:32.840
The bell...?

81
00:04:34.630 --> 00:04:36.130
One more time!

82
00:04:36.130 --> 00:04:38.800
One, two...!

83
00:04:40.010 --> 00:04:42.600
Pull!

84
00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:03.700
Dammit! We still don't
have enough people.

85
00:05:06.490 --> 00:05:09.000
This is the pride of
our ancestors—of Shandora.

86
00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:10.330
We'll do whatever it takes!

87
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:12.080
That's right!

88
00:05:12.080 --> 00:05:13.380
Give it all you got!

89
00:05:13.710 --> 00:05:17.090
One more time! One, two...!

90
00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:45.950
Pull with all your might!

91
00:05:53.170 --> 00:05:55.750
Rubber band?! This is
called a rubber band?!

92
00:05:55.750 --> 00:05:56.710
Yeah!

93
00:05:56.710 --> 00:06:01.550
Usopp's Rubber Bands of Doom did
90 percent of the damage to Giant Jack!

94
00:06:01.550 --> 00:06:03.720
– Whoa!
– Whoa! Incredible!

95
00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:05.930
And I'm the only one
in the world who has them.

96
00:06:05.930 --> 00:06:07.810
– Whoa!
– Whoa! Amazing!

97
00:06:10.810 --> 00:06:15.230
But... let's put that aside for now.
Next up is this iron sheet!

98
00:06:15.980 --> 00:06:20.070
Now, ladies and gentlemen!
This is no ordinary iron sheet!

99
00:06:20.070 --> 00:06:26.450
It's an iron sheet taken from our ship,
the Going Merry, that's survived

100
00:06:26.450 --> 00:06:29.910
the Grand Line, as well as Enel's attacks!
It's the "King of Iron Sheets"!

101
00:06:30.370 --> 00:06:32.410
How about it?!
You guys want iron, right?

102
00:06:32.410 --> 00:06:34.750
Wanna trade me some dials for this?

103
00:06:34.750 --> 00:06:36.250
No! I want this rubber band!

104
00:06:36.250 --> 00:06:38.380
I'll trade you for this rubber band!

105
00:06:38.380 --> 00:06:40.050
I want one too! Can I have one?!

106
00:06:40.050 --> 00:06:41.260
Me too!

107
00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:43.170
Whoa... Are they serious?!

108
00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:42.470
Give me one too!

109
00:06:42.470 --> 00:06:43.880
Me too!

110
00:06:57.730 --> 00:07:00.480
Shells! I got shells! Oh, yeah!

111
00:07:00.480 --> 00:07:05.660
Lucky, lucky! I got so lucky!

112
00:07:01.070 --> 00:07:02.900
You sure are in a good mood, Usopp.

113
00:07:04.280 --> 00:07:05.660
Did the trade go well?

114
00:07:07.570 --> 00:07:09.530
Hear that?

115
00:07:09.530 --> 00:07:12.500
I got a ton of dials!

116
00:07:13.080 --> 00:07:14.460
Just press here, and...

117
00:07:15.080 --> 00:07:16.000
out it comes!

118
00:07:16.920 --> 00:07:18.170
Good for you.

119
00:07:18.170 --> 00:07:19.290
Good for me!

120
00:07:19.290 --> 00:07:22.300
With this many dials,
I can do all sorts of stuff!

121
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:27.590
The Usopp Factory will
be running full steam!

122
00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:32.930
Hey, Zoro! What if I made your swords
into melon-flavored scent swords?

123
00:07:32.930 --> 00:07:35.480
That would spice up
your daily training!

124
00:07:35.480 --> 00:07:36.230
No thanks.

125
00:07:36.230 --> 00:07:37.350
Oh...

126
00:07:37.350 --> 00:07:41.690
Oh, yeah! I can upgrade
Nami's Climate Baton!

127
00:07:41.690 --> 00:07:44.650
And my slingshot will
be better than ever!

128
00:07:48.740 --> 00:07:51.240
So, where are Robin,
Luffy, and the others?

129
00:07:51.910 --> 00:07:55.910
Luffy and the others are still inside.
Robin went off somewhere.

130
00:08:01.040 --> 00:08:04.960
Well, I'll be... This snake
sure is a sound sleeper.

131
00:08:04.960 --> 00:08:07.430
He was dancing for days...

132
00:08:07.430 --> 00:08:10.050
Wonder what he was so happy about.

133
00:08:10.050 --> 00:08:12.010
In any case, they should
come out soon.

134
00:08:12.010 --> 00:08:14.310
He could be trouble if he wakes up.

135
00:08:14.310 --> 00:08:15.310
Huh?

136
00:08:15.310 --> 00:08:17.270
This sweetheart of a snake?

137
00:08:17.730 --> 00:08:21.230
Idiot! You just don't know
what a pain he can be!

138
00:08:21.230 --> 00:08:22.980
This sweetheart of a snake?

139
00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:28.400
Like I said, you didn't see how
pissed off this snake was.

140
00:08:28.400 --> 00:08:30.450
This sweetheart of a snake?

141
00:08:30.450 --> 00:08:33.030
Alright, come on, Usopp!

142
00:08:33.660 --> 00:08:35.750
This sweetheart of a snake?

143
00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:37.080
It was a tone dial!

144
00:08:37.080 --> 00:08:39.460
Enough with the stupid gag!

145
00:08:40.040 --> 00:08:44.380
Yeah, it's stupid! It's really stupid!

146
00:08:44.380 --> 00:08:47.550
What the heck?!
What does this snake eat?

147
00:08:47.550 --> 00:08:49.010
Are we there yet, Luffy?

148
00:08:49.010 --> 00:08:50.760
Look! There it is!

149
00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.550
Wow! Amazing!

150
00:08:52.550 --> 00:08:54.560
This is the real thing!

151
00:08:54.560 --> 00:08:57.810
So pretty! Just like the ones
we saw at the monkeys' house!

152
00:08:59.560 --> 00:09:01.810
See? See? See?!

153
00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:02.900
Look at all this!

154
00:09:03.610 --> 00:09:06.150
Isn't it awesome?!

155
00:09:14.740 --> 00:09:16.240
So this is the golden...

156
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:19.620
– How beautiful...
– Incredible...

157
00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:22.170
– I didn't expect it to be this...
– How magnificent.

158
00:09:22.750 --> 00:09:25.960
But one of the side
columns is broken.

159
00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:28.050
Yeah, it's been through a lot.

160
00:09:28.050 --> 00:09:30.880
Hey! Look there.

161
00:09:31.430 --> 00:09:34.050
So this is... the poneglyph...

162
00:09:35.010 --> 00:09:39.350
The stone that our ancestors
risked the city to protect!

163
00:09:40.770 --> 00:09:43.900
So what's written on it, Chief?

164
00:09:45.230 --> 00:09:47.860
It isn't for us to know...

165
00:09:51.280 --> 00:09:52.450
We just...

166
00:09:52.450 --> 00:09:55.030
"Hold the truth in your heart,
and speak not of it.

167
00:09:56.580 --> 00:09:59.620
We are the ones who weave history...

168
00:09:59.620 --> 00:10:01.710
with the sounding of the grand bell..."

169
00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:06.380
How do you know those words?

170
00:10:06.380 --> 00:10:09.380
They were carved on
the Shandian ruins.

171
00:10:09.380 --> 00:10:13.010
So you were the guardians who
protected this for generations.

172
00:10:19.600 --> 00:10:23.770
Could it be... You can
read those symbols?!

173
00:10:28.150 --> 00:10:32.030
Poseidon, the ancient weapon
named after a god...

174
00:10:32.030 --> 00:10:33.570
Its location...

175
00:10:33.570 --> 00:10:34.860
What?! What's that?!

176
00:10:34.860 --> 00:10:35.490
"Ancient"?!

177
00:10:35.490 --> 00:10:37.280
Ancient weapon?

178
00:10:37.280 --> 00:10:39.700
Why would they write
something like that?!

179
00:10:39.700 --> 00:10:41.040
Yeah...

180
00:10:41.750 --> 00:10:46.580
Another weapon... different from
the Pluton I read about in Alabasta...

181
00:10:47.290 --> 00:10:49.210
To think that such dangerous things

182
00:10:49.210 --> 00:10:52.590
still slumber somewhere
in the world...!

183
00:10:53.800 --> 00:10:55.300
I should've known better.

184
00:10:56.050 --> 00:10:59.350
This isn't what I've been searching for.

185
00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:00.810
Hey, you!

186
00:11:00.810 --> 00:11:03.770
Aren't there more of those symbols
engraved next to it?!

187
00:11:04.140 --> 00:11:05.190
What?!

188
00:11:08.860 --> 00:11:12.110
"Gol D. Roger"...!

189
00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:15.030
What is this?!

190
00:11:16.610 --> 00:11:19.450
I made it here.

191
00:11:19.450 --> 00:11:22.660
I will guide this text to
the ends of the world.

192
00:11:22.660 --> 00:11:25.410
Pirate Gol D. Roger.

193
00:11:27.630 --> 00:11:28.670
The King of the Pirates...!

194
00:11:29.380 --> 00:11:33.590
Could this mean that he came
to this sky island, too?!

195
00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:39.090
No, more importantly,
how did he know this script?

196
00:11:41.850 --> 00:11:43.970
Did I hear "Roger"?

197
00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:45.730
You know him?!

198
00:11:45.730 --> 00:11:51.020
He's a Blue Sea pirate who came to
this sky over twenty years ago.

199
00:11:51.610 --> 00:11:53.780
So his name is engraved there?

200
00:11:53.780 --> 00:11:54.400
Yes.

201
00:11:55.150 --> 00:11:59.070
I don't know how
he reached this bell...

202
00:11:59.990 --> 00:12:02.910
but this is definitive proof that he did.

203
00:12:03.450 --> 00:12:08.000
Come to think of it, there are
two kinds of poneglyph stones.

204
00:12:08.920 --> 00:12:13.500
Ones with information,
and others that mark locations.

205
00:12:13.500 --> 00:12:16.380
This is the type with information.

206
00:12:22.970 --> 00:12:25.350
"I made it here.

207
00:12:25.980 --> 00:12:28.480
I will guide this text to
the ends of the world."

208
00:12:30.350 --> 00:12:31.940
Guide this text...

209
00:12:33.520 --> 00:12:34.780
Guide...

210
00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:40.490
Could it be...?!

211
00:12:40.490 --> 00:12:42.450
Could the Rio Poneglyph be...?!

212
00:12:48.080 --> 00:12:48.910
Chief...

213
00:12:49.670 --> 00:12:53.670
This poneglyph has
already fulfilled its role!

214
00:12:53.670 --> 00:12:55.050
It has?!

215
00:12:56.840 --> 00:12:57.720
Yes.

216
00:12:57.720 --> 00:13:02.260
I believe the informational poneglyphs
scattered around the world

217
00:13:02.260 --> 00:13:08.390
can be combined into a single text
that will fill in the Void Century.

218
00:13:09.980 --> 00:13:14.230
In other words, connecting
the full text creates...

219
00:13:14.230 --> 00:13:19.070
something never seen before:
the Rio Poneglyph.

220
00:13:20.360 --> 00:13:22.530
Gol D. Roger, King of the Pirates,

221
00:13:23.160 --> 00:13:26.950
must have delivered this
text to its destination.

222
00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:34.500
So it's no longer...

223
00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:35.500
Then...

224
00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:36.300
Hm?

225
00:13:38.090 --> 00:13:43.470
We... don't have to...
fight any longer?

226
00:13:46.100 --> 00:13:50.890
I see... So the wish of
our ancestors has been fulfilled?

227
00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:53.060
– Chief!
– Chief!

228
00:13:53.060 --> 00:13:54.610
Are you all right?!

229
00:13:54.610 --> 00:13:59.360
Good... Good... So our
duty has been fulfilled!

230
00:14:01.030 --> 00:14:02.240
Yes.

231
00:14:03.110 --> 00:14:04.950
Which means I, too,

232
00:14:04.950 --> 00:14:09.500
have to guide the text on
the poneglyphs I've read...

233
00:14:10.660 --> 00:14:14.000
to the end of the
Grand Line... to Laugh Tale...

234
00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:24.050
Young lady, that straw hat boy gives
me the same feeling Roger once did.

235
00:14:25.050 --> 00:14:27.220
But perhaps it's just my imagination.

236
00:14:27.680 --> 00:14:30.060
His name is Monkey D. Luffy.

237
00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:32.060
He never fails to keep my interest.

238
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:36.610
D? I see. So they share
that letter in their names.

239
00:14:39.440 --> 00:14:44.070
Yes... and I'm sure it's quite
important to our history.

240
00:14:45.660 --> 00:14:46.620
By the way, miss...

241
00:14:47.530 --> 00:14:50.370
You all wanted gold, right?

242
00:14:50.370 --> 00:14:53.830
You said it's more valuable
than vearth in the Blue Sea.

243
00:14:53.830 --> 00:14:54.710
Yes.

244
00:14:54.710 --> 00:14:57.750
Since we can't give you the bell,

245
00:14:57.750 --> 00:14:59.290
how about the bell column?

246
00:14:59.290 --> 00:15:01.050
That's a good idea!

247
00:15:01.050 --> 00:15:05.050
We have to show our appreciation
to you guys somehow, you know.

248
00:15:05.050 --> 00:15:05.970
That's right!

249
00:15:05.970 --> 00:15:06.930
We insist!

250
00:15:06.930 --> 00:15:09.890
Are you sure?! They'll
be happy to hear that!

251
00:15:10.310 --> 00:15:11.600
Yes!

252
00:15:12.980 --> 00:15:17.150
Alright, then! Let's bring
this to the Blue Sea people!

253
00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:19.400
Wrap it with cloth! It's hard to carry!

254
00:15:19.400 --> 00:15:21.780
Let's give it to the people
who saved our land!

255
00:15:21.780 --> 00:15:23.650
Man, this thing's huge...

256
00:15:30.780 --> 00:15:35.290
What's Robin doing? She's late!

257
00:15:35.870 --> 00:15:37.460
Oh, man! I'm hungry!

258
00:15:39.380 --> 00:15:43.260
This place sure emptied out.
What's going on?

259
00:15:43.670 --> 00:15:47.220
Where did all those
guerrillas and angels go?

260
00:15:47.220 --> 00:15:51.890
Well, it's better they aren't here.
They'll chase us if they find out!

261
00:15:51.890 --> 00:15:56.270
We're about to steal
all this gold and make a run for it.

262
00:15:56.270 --> 00:15:57.900
They won't just let us escape!

263
00:15:57.900 --> 00:16:01.690
Nami and Conis are preparing
the ship, but we still have to hurry.

264
00:16:01.690 --> 00:16:04.280
Before that, Sanji, do we
have something to eat?

265
00:16:04.280 --> 00:16:05.490
Yeah, on the ship.

266
00:16:06.280 --> 00:16:09.200
But you've gotta have
a little snack to munch on, right?

267
00:16:09.200 --> 00:16:10.530
Gimme!
What a pain!

268
00:16:10.530 --> 00:16:12.870
I can't give you what
I don't have! Let it go!
We don't have to wait
for that lady, do we?

269
00:16:12.870 --> 00:16:14.870
I'm gonna go on ahead
and get on board.

270
00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:16.250
Idiot! Don't!

271
00:16:16.250 --> 00:16:17.000
Idiot!

272
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:18.080
Idiot Moss Head!

273
00:16:18.080 --> 00:16:19.290
Moss Head idiot!

274
00:16:20.630 --> 00:16:24.760
You won't make it three steps alone
in that forest without getting lost!

275
00:16:28.430 --> 00:16:29.720
Hey, look! It's Robin!

276
00:16:31.510 --> 00:16:33.600
Robin!

277
00:16:34.260 --> 00:16:36.850
Hey, Robin!

278
00:16:36.850 --> 00:16:40.600
Hurry, hurry! Make a run for it!
We stole some gold!

279
00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:42.110
Zip it, moron!

280
00:16:42.110 --> 00:16:43.520
Try looking behind her!

281
00:16:43.940 --> 00:16:46.440
They're all coming back at once!

282
00:16:47.570 --> 00:16:48.900
There's a ton of them!

283
00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:56.580
This is bad! This is bad!
This is super bad!

284
00:16:56.580 --> 00:16:58.710
And what's that? A huge cannon?!

285
00:16:59.410 --> 00:17:00.170
It's gotta be!

286
00:17:00.580 --> 00:17:03.340
They came back all at once!

287
00:17:03.790 --> 00:17:05.550
Hurry to the ship!

288
00:17:05.880 --> 00:17:08.470
We can't stay here anymore!

289
00:17:09.720 --> 00:17:11.640
Check this out! We got a good haul!

290
00:17:11.640 --> 00:17:13.970
The bag's stuffed! We're rich!

291
00:17:13.970 --> 00:17:17.390
What? They all have their bags on!

292
00:17:17.390 --> 00:17:20.440
Don't tell me... they're
leaving already?!

293
00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:22.850
Hey, stop, you guys! Stop!

294
00:17:22.850 --> 00:17:26.480
Hey! Stop! Stop, you guys!

295
00:17:23.190 --> 00:17:25.070
See?! They caught us!

296
00:17:25.070 --> 00:17:26.480
Run!

297
00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:30.280
Time to strike a pose
and make a speech!

298
00:17:31.660 --> 00:17:34.700
You can ask us to stop all you want!

299
00:17:34.700 --> 00:17:36.790
Yeah! Tell them, Usopp!

300
00:17:38.290 --> 00:17:41.290
We risked our lives to come
all the way to this sky island!

301
00:17:40.790 --> 00:17:42.500
That's right!

302
00:17:41.290 --> 00:17:44.040
And we've found the
legendary City of Gold!

303
00:17:43.040 --> 00:17:46.090
Robin! Hurry up! We'll get caught!

304
00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:49.130
Would you really expect proud pirates
like us to go back empty-handed?!

305
00:17:49.590 --> 00:17:51.970
What?! Caught?!
What's he talking about?

306
00:17:52.340 --> 00:17:54.470
All we want to do is thank them!

307
00:17:54.470 --> 00:17:58.430
Hey miss, aren't you guys
gonna take this gold?

308
00:18:01.890 --> 00:18:02.850
I guess not!

309
00:18:02.850 --> 00:18:04.730
– What?!
– What?!

310
00:18:04.730 --> 00:18:06.150
Oh no!

311
00:18:09.650 --> 00:18:11.950
Run!

312
00:18:10.530 --> 00:18:14.070
– Hey! Wait!
– Hey! Wait!

313
00:18:14.070 --> 00:18:17.490
They're all after us! Too scary!

314
00:18:18.290 --> 00:18:20.450
How was that?! Wasn't I cool?!

315
00:18:20.450 --> 00:18:22.870
Yeah! Well done!

316
00:18:23.620 --> 00:18:26.290
Robin my love! Hurry!

317
00:18:26.630 --> 00:18:29.760
– Hey! Come back!
– Hey! Come back!

318
00:18:29.760 --> 00:18:31.420
Guys!

319
00:18:31.420 --> 00:18:35.340
Keep running all the way
to the end of the sky!

320
00:18:35.340 --> 00:18:39.100
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

321
00:18:42.750 --> 00:18:48.270
When you're lost and alone, call out and lead me to your side

322
00:18:48.490 --> 00:18:53.690
As you wander far from home, you search the sky and never hide

323
00:18:53.690 --> 00:18:56.490
You are so much like the moon

324
00:18:56.490 --> 00:19:01.140
Calmer than a star, your twinkling's lost

325
00:19:04.590 --> 00:19:13.540
A deep reflection shines, you slowly leave, fading, and what's the cost?

326
00:19:13.600 --> 00:19:18.770
Stay as you are, don't lose your way

327
00:19:18.770 --> 00:19:27.080
Let my words guide you, and look ahead until the day!

328
00:19:27.720 --> 00:19:33.970
Don't give up on your dreams, through endless nights they come to you

329
00:19:33.970 --> 00:19:39.590
If you stop, you'll never see them shining through!

330
00:19:40.830 --> 00:19:45.360
Will you return? Maybe not... Will you learn? I hope you do

331
00:19:45.360 --> 00:19:51.750
Please put your past to rest, and live your life anew.
